main event: A single fast-moving large object was observed in the sky over Sequim, Washington on September 2, 1955.
interesting points: The object was described as being the size of a large coin and moving very fast.
A sound was heard during the sighting, which lasted for 2 minutes.
The sighting was reported by both civilian and military (Ground Observer Corps) witnesses.
The object's course was not specified, but it was classified as a 'UFOB' (Unidentified Flying Object).
The report was forwarded according to Air Force Regulation 205-2 for further investigation.
